pr_review_comment_body:
pretty sure you don't have to add the bind if you [wrote the functions using () => syntax ](https://medium.com/@machnicki/handle-events-in-react-with-arrow-functions-ede88184bbb#.2dlb31qok)

```
handleUrlChange = (e) => {
   ....
}
```

this dictionary is global. Common python bug.
To fix it, use `finished_parts=None` and
```python
if finished_parts is None:
    finished_parts = {}
```

Can combine into
```js
if (this.pageState.taskList && this.pageState.taskList.length) {
  return true;
}
return false;
```
